      },
      {
        "metric": "The B57 and B58 earn 4★ out of 5 [BMW‑VERIFIED], based on 1,000+ combined UK enquiries. They are widely considered BMW’s most reliable modern sixes, with fewer catastrophic failures than the N47/N57.",
        "value": "3. What is the most common BMW B57/B58 failure?"
      },
      {
        "metric": "Coolant system issues are the most common — water pump leaks, expansion tank cracks, and plastic fittings failing. These typically occur from 60,000–120,000 miles and are relatively inexpensive to fix.",
        "value": "4. Which BMW models use the B57 or B58 engine?"
      },
      {
        "metric": "The B57 diesel powers 20d, 30d, 40d models across the 1–8 Series and X‑range; the B58 petrol powers 30i, 40i and M Performance models like the M340i, M440i, M240i, X3 M40i and Z4 M40i.",
        "value": "5. How long does the BMW B57/B58 engine last?"
      },
      {
        "metric": "With proper servicing (10,000‑mile oil changes using BMW Longlife‑17 spec), both can comfortably exceed 180,000–220,000 miles. The B58’s open‑deck block and B57’s steel‑piston design are built for longevity.",
